Dr. Richard Alan Miller developed the rst AI on a 360 back in 1973 and presented his paper

hologram of 4-space.!
Dr. Miller is a prodigy, and his abilities gave us an idea of which way to go. He trained under
many Nobel laureates. When they sent him to Princeton he was with Roger Penrose. At MIT he
had Charlie Muses, Albert Senskorkis, and Edward Edward Horton. They were educating him
to take that Universe to the next level, which he did was going from a quantum mechanical
system to a holographic system. He tells us that in the sciences every time you do something
you start with assumed truths. The assumptions you have open some doors, but close others,
therefore you need to have the broadest worldview as possible.!
I decided to look at my theory of inertia and proton-seconds through the lens of what these
people were doing at that time in terms of illustrations. My theory in my paper The Moon: Key
to the Universe."
